# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your key.
# Most people never touch this file — the app has an in-app key form
# (first launch walks you through it). This is the power-user / CLI path.

# Google Gemini API key (required for analysis).
# Get a free one at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# The key stays on your machine — it's only ever sent to Google's own API
# at analyze time, never to any Vellum server.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Optional — the model used for analysis. Defaults to gemini-2.5-pro.
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro

# Optional — comma-separated fallbacks, tried in order only when the primary
# is overloaded (503 "high demand"). Defaults to the two lightest 2.5 tiers.
# GEMINI_FALLBACK_MODELS=gemini-2.5-flash,gemini-2.5-flash-lite

# Optional — long-recording segmentation (TASK-9). A file over MAX_BYTES is
# split into overlapping segments for Gemini (the 2 GB File API limit). Defaults:
# ~1.8 GB budget, 12 s overlap. Set MAX_BYTES tiny to force segmentation on a
# short clip when testing (e.g. 600000 turns a ~10 s clip into 2 segments).
# VELLUM_SEGMENT_MAX_BYTES=
# VELLUM_SEGMENT_OVERLAP_SEC=
